org.croudtrip.api.gcm

Class GcmConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.croudtrip.api.gcm.GcmConstants

  • public class GcmConstants
extends java.lang.Object
    That class contains the common gcm tags that are used by our server to send messages to the client. The client has to use these tags to extract the sent information from the server message. Created by Frederik Simon on 07.05.2015.

      • GCM_TYPE

        public static final java.lang.String GCM_TYPE
        This tag is sent with every message so that you can check what the type of a message is The content of this message data is the string that describes the following message (e.g. GCM_MSG_JOIN_REQUEST, GCM_MSG_REQUECT_ACCEPTED etc.).

      • GCM_MSG_REQUEST_ERROR

        public static final java.lang.String GCM_MSG_REQUEST_ERROR
        Messages with this tag are sent to the passenger, if there is something wrong with the requested trip (e.g. the trip does not exist anymore). It could be handled in the same way as GCM_MSG_REQUEST_DECLINED, or there is a different error message.
